WEBVTT

00:07.333 --> 00:09.417
♪ Ben 10 ♪

00:10.458 --> 00:12.542
♪ Ben 10 ♪

00:13.667 --> 00:15.917
♪ Ben 10 ♪

00:16.875 --> 00:18.958
♪ Ben 10 ♪

00:21.542 --> 00:25.375
♪♪

00:28.417 --> 00:29.685
- [ Crash ] - Oh!

00:29.792 --> 00:30.644
- Huh? - Freeze!

00:30.750 --> 00:31.333
Ugh!

00:31.417 --> 00:32.667
Okay, boys.

00:32.750 --> 00:33.917
You know what to do.

00:34.000 --> 00:36.083
[ All chuckle ]

00:36.417 --> 00:37.625
[ Grunting ]

00:37.708 --> 00:39.625
[ Alarm ringing ]

00:39.708 --> 00:41.792
[ Shing! ]

00:43.167 --> 00:44.500
[ Coins clink ]

00:44.583 --> 00:45.602
Everyone,

00:45.626 --> 00:46.667
empty your pockets!

00:46.750 --> 00:48.477
- Yeah, - give us the goods.

00:48.583 --> 00:50.667
Heatblast: Get squashed!

00:51.292 --> 00:52.311
You can't

00:52.335 --> 00:53.375
take the heat...

00:54.958 --> 00:55.977
stay out

00:56.001 --> 00:57.042
of the bank, boys.

00:57.125 --> 00:58.477
Did you catch that line?

00:58.501 --> 00:59.875
Cool, right?

00:59.958 --> 01:01.373
Normally it's "kitchen,"

01:01.397 --> 01:02.833
but I switched it up.

01:02.917 --> 01:03.957
Gwen: Of course I got it.

01:03.981 --> 01:05.042
On your right!

01:06.917 --> 01:09.083
The camera loves a hero.

01:09.167 --> 01:11.185
- You're out of frame, hero. - To your left.

01:11.292 --> 01:12.708
Oh, no problem.

01:12.792 --> 01:14.125
Your other left.

01:14.208 --> 01:15.667
How's this?

01:15.750 --> 01:16.833
Perfect.

01:16.917 --> 01:18.060
- Okay, now, - go get them.

01:18.167 --> 01:19.417
Uhh...

01:19.500 --> 01:21.375
You're going down!

01:21.458 --> 01:22.581
Wait. What's

01:22.605 --> 01:23.750
my motivation again?

01:23.833 --> 01:25.852
Um, stopping those bank robbers

01:25.876 --> 01:27.917
from stealing my 401(k)?

01:28.000 --> 01:29.458
Is that enough?

01:29.542 --> 01:30.936
I mean, I know

01:30.960 --> 01:32.375
how I feel about bad guys,

01:32.458 --> 01:34.625
but what is a 401(k)?

01:34.708 --> 01:35.977
What does it mean

01:36.001 --> 01:37.292
to Heatblast?

01:39.833 --> 01:41.519
- Uh, you're letting them - get away.

01:41.625 --> 01:42.706
No, this is where

01:42.730 --> 01:43.833
they tremble in fear,

01:43.917 --> 01:45.708
and Heatblast says...

01:45.792 --> 01:48.083
Justice burns!

01:48.167 --> 01:50.250
[ Crash ]

01:51.542 --> 01:54.292
[ All grumbling ]

01:54.375 --> 01:55.415
[ Sirens wailing ]

01:55.439 --> 01:56.500
Uh, fear not, citizens.

01:56.583 --> 01:58.123
I can still catch them.

01:58.147 --> 01:59.708
Yeah!

01:59.792 --> 01:59.792
- [ Smack, crash, shatter ] - Oh! Excuse me.

01:59.792 --> 02:01.500
Pardon me.

02:01.583 --> 02:03.102
- Woman: - My purse is on fire!

02:03.208 --> 02:04.935
- Aah! I'm sorry! - I'm sorry!

02:05.042 --> 02:06.290
[ Chuckles ]

02:06.314 --> 02:07.583
Classic.

02:08.625 --> 02:10.167
Ohh. Weak.

02:10.250 --> 02:11.811
We're supposed to be making

02:11.835 --> 02:13.417
the coolest action movie ever.

02:13.500 --> 02:15.167
Instead, we got this.

02:15.250 --> 02:16.623
<i>Don't worry!</i>

02:16.647 --> 02:18.042
<i>I can still catch them!</i>

02:18.125 --> 02:19.560
<i>- Ohh!</i> - [ <i>Thuds</i> ]

02:19.667 --> 02:21.519
- [ Laughs ] - This scene?

02:21.625 --> 02:22.831
But it's perfect!

02:22.855 --> 02:24.083
That's comedy gold.

02:24.167 --> 02:25.915
It's a terrible stunt, and

02:25.939 --> 02:27.708
we're making an action movie.

02:27.792 --> 02:28.873
Say it with me...

02:28.897 --> 02:30.000
"comedy."

02:30.083 --> 02:31.935
- Oh, you're ruining - my action film!

02:32.042 --> 02:33.644
- Your film?! - I bought that phone,

02:33.750 --> 02:34.936
Which makes me

02:34.960 --> 02:36.167
the producer of this film.

02:36.250 --> 02:37.625
Can I offer my input?

02:37.708 --> 02:38.708
Both: No!

02:38.750 --> 02:40.208
Overruled.

02:40.292 --> 02:41.809
- You both seem - to have forgotten about

02:41.833 --> 02:43.602
- That bug gang - you let escape.

02:43.708 --> 02:45.310
- I know you kids are - having fun,

02:45.417 --> 02:46.811
But don't let your ego keep you

02:46.835 --> 02:48.250
from doing the right thing.

02:48.333 --> 02:49.792
You're right, Grandpa.

02:49.875 --> 02:52.123
That's not what a true

02:52.147 --> 02:54.417
super-cool action star would do.

02:54.500 --> 02:55.500
Ben.

02:55.583 --> 02:56.915
I will catch

02:56.939 --> 02:58.292
that crazy bug gang...

02:58.375 --> 02:59.352
Please let that be

02:59.376 --> 03:00.376
the end of the sentence.

03:00.458 --> 03:01.560
While making

03:01.584 --> 03:02.708
the world's coolest...

03:02.792 --> 03:04.477
Chu! Chu! Pew! Pew!

03:04.501 --> 03:06.208
Action blockbuster!

03:06.292 --> 03:08.125
Wha-chaa!

03:08.208 --> 03:09.310
You guys are welcome

03:09.334 --> 03:10.458
to tag along and be my crew.

03:10.542 --> 03:11.644
[ Laughs ]

03:11.668 --> 03:12.792
See how funny you are?

03:12.875 --> 03:14.727
- [ Laughs ] - I'm not funny.

03:14.833 --> 03:16.644
- With you acting - and me directing,

03:16.750 --> 03:18.311
We can make

03:18.335 --> 03:19.917
comedy history.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.583
[ Laughs ]

03:22.667 --> 03:24.477
- Marvelous. - Just...

03:24.583 --> 03:25.644
[ Ant clears throat ]

03:25.668 --> 03:26.750
Queen Bee?

03:26.833 --> 03:27.958
What?!

03:28.042 --> 03:30.167
Where's our cut?

03:30.250 --> 03:33.167
Of course, darlings.

03:33.250 --> 03:35.333
There you are.

03:36.292 --> 03:37.748
Now get out of my light and

03:37.772 --> 03:39.250
start planning our next heist.

03:39.333 --> 03:40.935
Blah, blah,

03:40.959 --> 03:42.583
"Start planning our next heist."

03:42.667 --> 03:43.917
What was that?

03:44.000 --> 03:45.144
Uh, nothing!

03:45.168 --> 03:46.333
Nothing!

03:48.708 --> 03:49.768
- [ Beeping ] - What you are about to see

03:49.792 --> 03:51.125
Is the absolute coolest thing

03:51.208 --> 03:52.958
ever to happen on camera.

03:53.042 --> 03:54.417
Are you ready?

03:54.500 --> 03:56.000
I can't hear you!

03:56.083 --> 03:57.290
Not over the sound of your own

03:57.314 --> 03:58.542
delusional thought.

03:58.625 --> 04:00.583
Ohhhhh!

04:00.667 --> 04:02.125
Ignore the intern.

04:02.208 --> 04:04.165
Uh, I think you mean

04:04.189 --> 04:06.167
the director... of sick burns!

04:06.250 --> 04:07.708
Yooooooooo!

04:07.792 --> 04:09.394
- I am the director, - though.

04:09.500 --> 04:10.852
Watch in amazement as I use

04:10.876 --> 04:12.250
my awesome powers

04:12.333 --> 04:14.060
- to track - the slippery crooks.

04:14.167 --> 04:15.165
Uh, yeah, no.

04:15.189 --> 04:16.208
What?

04:16.292 --> 04:17.809
- The audience won't be able - to see anything

04:17.833 --> 04:19.809
- If your big head's in the frame - the whole time.

04:19.833 --> 04:20.915
Give me the phone,

04:20.939 --> 04:22.042
and you investigate.

04:22.125 --> 04:23.456
No! You're gonna ruin

04:23.480 --> 04:24.833
my awesome action movie!

04:24.917 --> 04:26.602
- Comedy! - Action.

04:26.708 --> 04:27.917
[ Goofy ] Comedy!

04:28.000 --> 04:29.792
[ Groans, sighs ]

04:29.875 --> 04:31.292
This scene's getting slow.

04:31.375 --> 04:32.958
XLR8 can help with that.

04:33.042 --> 04:34.250
[ Beeping ]

04:34.333 --> 04:35.665
♪ Just four letters,

04:35.689 --> 04:37.042
he's so great ♪

04:37.125 --> 04:38.833
♪ Need for speed ♪

04:38.917 --> 04:40.667
Aah!

04:40.750 --> 04:41.833
Grey Matter?!

04:41.917 --> 04:43.810
- Watch, - you betrayed me!

04:43.917 --> 04:45.373
And that's when Gwen

04:45.397 --> 04:46.875
got promoted back to director.

04:46.958 --> 04:47.956
Give it back,

04:47.980 --> 04:49.000
Philistine!

04:49.083 --> 04:50.352
Listen, if we work together,

04:50.376 --> 04:51.667
we can...

04:51.750 --> 04:52.873
No!

04:52.897 --> 04:54.042
My movie!

04:54.125 --> 04:55.102
Mine.

04:55.126 --> 04:56.126
Mine!

04:56.208 --> 04:57.790
Sometimes, I really

04:57.814 --> 04:59.417
don't get you, Watch.

04:59.500 --> 05:00.792
Advantage!

05:00.875 --> 05:02.958
[ Both grunting ]

05:04.500 --> 05:05.519
Wait.

05:05.543 --> 05:06.583
Did you see that?

05:08.458 --> 05:09.542
Right there.

05:09.625 --> 05:11.125
I didn't see anything.

05:11.208 --> 05:12.415
Gwen,

05:12.439 --> 05:13.667
zoom in and enhance.

05:13.750 --> 05:15.833
O... kay.

05:17.833 --> 05:19.560
- Ah! I can't believe - that worked.

05:19.667 --> 05:21.435
- Aha! - They went underground.

05:21.542 --> 05:23.123
There must be some kind of super

05:23.147 --> 05:24.750
secret evil underground bug lair

05:24.833 --> 05:26.309
- hidden carefully - beneath the earth...

05:26.333 --> 05:27.540
The setting

05:27.564 --> 05:28.792
for our next action scene.

05:28.875 --> 05:30.250
[ Sighs ] Fine.

05:30.333 --> 05:31.768
- But we'll also get - those bug guys

05:31.792 --> 05:33.643
- And get everyone - their money back too, right?

05:33.667 --> 05:35.792
Whaaaa-ka-cha-cha!

05:35.875 --> 05:38.019
- No problem. - I mean, how hard's it gonna be?

05:38.125 --> 05:39.435
- There's only - three of them.

05:39.542 --> 05:40.644
I want those diamonds

05:40.668 --> 05:41.792
sorted by carat,

05:41.875 --> 05:43.144
and if you're off

05:43.168 --> 05:44.458
by a tenth of a milligram,

05:44.542 --> 05:47.144
I will have you dipped in honey

05:47.168 --> 05:49.792
and dropped in a bear cave.

05:49.875 --> 05:51.727
Oh, darling,

05:51.751 --> 05:53.625
what have you got there?

05:53.708 --> 05:55.792
Uhh, a necklace?

05:55.875 --> 05:58.206
Yes, a necklace...

05:58.230 --> 06:00.583
that belongs <i>to me!</i>

06:00.667 --> 06:02.750
[ Rumbling ]

06:04.000 --> 06:05.394
You three are really starting

06:05.418 --> 06:06.833
to bug me.

06:06.917 --> 06:07.977
[ Chuckles ]

06:08.001 --> 06:09.083
Did you get that, Gwen?

06:09.167 --> 06:10.727
Um, yeah, but we might

06:10.751 --> 06:12.333
have to rewrite that line.

06:12.417 --> 06:13.935
- [ Guns cock ] - Huh?

06:14.042 --> 06:15.500
Ohhhh.

06:15.583 --> 06:16.623
What have you done

06:16.647 --> 06:17.708
to my lair?!

06:17.792 --> 06:19.394
Man, you guys really like

06:19.418 --> 06:21.042
your bug suits.

06:21.125 --> 06:22.436
Uh, Ben, I don't think

06:22.460 --> 06:23.792
she's wearing a bug suit.

06:23.875 --> 06:24.998
Oh. [ Gasps ] Wait! Wait!

06:25.022 --> 06:26.167
[ Gasps ] I got this.

06:26.250 --> 06:27.769
Underground lair, buggy

06:27.793 --> 06:29.333
bad guys, creepy bee lady boss.

06:29.417 --> 06:30.542
Action!

06:30.625 --> 06:31.748
Hey, did you hear

06:31.772 --> 06:32.917
the <i>buzz?</i>

06:33.792 --> 06:35.707
You better <i>"bee-have"</i> yourself

06:35.731 --> 06:37.667
and turn yourself in...

06:39.250 --> 06:40.727
or I'm gonna make you

06:40.751 --> 06:42.250
<i>"bee"</i> gone.

06:42.333 --> 06:43.935
- Did you get that? - Let me see.

06:44.042 --> 06:45.882
- Ben, I really don't think - this is the time.

06:45.958 --> 06:47.667
You weren't filming?!

06:47.750 --> 06:49.375
You've broken my ceiling.

06:49.458 --> 06:50.956
Now you've ruined...

06:50.980 --> 06:52.500
my lighting scheme!

06:52.583 --> 06:53.917
Drones, attack!

06:54.000 --> 06:55.394
Gwen, you better get

06:55.418 --> 06:56.833
my sweet action moves.

06:57.708 --> 06:59.310
- Get him! - [ All grunting ]

06:59.417 --> 07:00.561
Ugh! Get up!

07:00.585 --> 07:01.750
What are you doing?!

07:01.833 --> 07:02.998
Ohh.

07:03.022 --> 07:04.208
Ohh, boohoo.

07:04.292 --> 07:05.707
I don't care!

07:05.731 --> 07:07.167
Get that... thing!

07:09.500 --> 07:10.602
You guys are

07:10.626 --> 07:11.750
<i>"bee-yond"</i> terrible.

07:11.833 --> 07:13.042
[ Gasps ] Whoa!

07:13.125 --> 07:14.331
Ben, there's too many of them!

07:14.355 --> 07:15.583
Get serious!

07:15.667 --> 07:16.417
Waah!

07:16.500 --> 07:18.833
I'm so serious!

07:18.917 --> 07:20.936
This is

07:20.960 --> 07:23.000
a serious action movie!

07:23.083 --> 07:23.875
Yeah!

07:23.958 --> 07:25.685
- Did you get that? - Ugh!

07:25.792 --> 07:26.958
[ Muffled ] Did you get it?

07:27.042 --> 07:28.227
She didn't.

07:28.251 --> 07:29.458
Missing something?

07:29.542 --> 07:31.042
<i>I</i> got her instead.

07:31.125 --> 07:32.250
Gwen!

07:32.333 --> 07:33.500
You made a mistake

07:33.583 --> 07:35.394
- destroying the roof - of my lovely lair.

07:35.500 --> 07:36.623
Now, to decide

07:36.647 --> 07:37.792
on proper retribu...

07:37.875 --> 07:39.792
Uh, excuse me.

07:39.875 --> 07:41.042
Could you move?

07:41.125 --> 07:43.167
You're in my light!

07:43.250 --> 07:44.581
<i>You</i> are making <i>me</i>

07:44.605 --> 07:45.958
look bad.

07:46.042 --> 07:47.165
<i>You're gonna ruin</i>

07:47.189 --> 07:48.333
<i>my awesome action movie!</i>

07:48.417 --> 07:49.708
My movie!

07:49.792 --> 07:51.477
- Mine. - Mine!

07:51.583 --> 07:53.250
Ugh. Wow.

07:53.333 --> 07:54.685
Did I really sound

07:54.709 --> 07:56.083
like that?

07:56.167 --> 07:58.375
It's perfect!

07:58.458 --> 08:00.310
Our super undercover

08:00.334 --> 08:02.208
location hunt was a success!

08:02.292 --> 08:04.165
We can make our super-awesome

08:04.189 --> 08:06.083
new movie, and most importantly,

08:06.167 --> 08:07.748
we found

08:07.772 --> 08:09.375
the perfect new star.

08:09.458 --> 08:11.333
Tell her, director!

08:11.417 --> 08:13.227
He's right.

08:13.251 --> 08:15.083
You've got the face of, uh...

08:15.167 --> 08:17.102
- You were made - for the big screen.

08:17.208 --> 08:19.248
Oh, well, I did spend some time

08:19.272 --> 08:21.333
at a local community theater

08:21.417 --> 08:23.269
- before I turned - to a life of crime.

08:23.375 --> 08:24.583
Oh, yeah, I can tell.

08:24.667 --> 08:26.292
You're a natural.

08:26.375 --> 08:28.292
[ Laughs ] Oh, stop.

08:28.375 --> 08:29.500
No, it's true.

08:29.583 --> 08:31.102
You really have

08:31.126 --> 08:32.667
that special something.

08:32.750 --> 08:34.042
[ Laughs ]

08:34.125 --> 08:35.644
Psst! You guys have

08:35.668 --> 08:37.208
some operation going here.

08:37.292 --> 08:38.644
Too bad you're not appreciated

08:38.668 --> 08:40.042
for your hard work.

08:40.125 --> 08:41.417
What do you mean?

08:41.500 --> 08:43.167
Eh, we get appreciated.

08:43.250 --> 08:45.019
Oh, sure, when you're

08:45.043 --> 08:46.833
not getting yelled at by a diva!

08:46.917 --> 08:47.915
You're working

08:47.939 --> 08:48.958
your buggy limbs off.

08:49.042 --> 08:50.500
What's she doing?

08:50.583 --> 08:52.042
[ Laughs ]

08:52.125 --> 08:53.667
Oh, now the right.

08:53.750 --> 08:54.790
Oh! [ Laughs ]

08:54.814 --> 08:55.875
Oh!

08:55.958 --> 08:57.917
Gettin' her close-up.

08:58.000 --> 08:59.186
And keepin'

08:59.210 --> 09:00.417
all the dough!

09:00.500 --> 09:01.561
Doesn't seem fair,

09:01.585 --> 09:02.667
does it?

09:02.750 --> 09:03.500
No.

09:03.583 --> 09:04.500
You know what, fellas?

09:04.583 --> 09:05.792
I think we should write

09:05.875 --> 09:07.519
a strongly worded

09:07.543 --> 09:09.208
letter of disapproval.

09:09.292 --> 09:11.519
Or... you could revolt and take

09:11.543 --> 09:13.792
all the loot for yourselves.

09:13.875 --> 09:15.310
- Yes! - Oh, yeah!

09:15.417 --> 09:16.810
- We're gonna need - a bigger bag!

09:16.917 --> 09:18.540
You know, you should consider

09:18.564 --> 09:20.208
a life of crime.

09:20.292 --> 09:22.227
- Thanks, - but I don't need a job.

09:22.333 --> 09:24.081
[ Dramatic music plays ]

09:24.105 --> 09:25.875
I'm... an action star!

09:25.958 --> 09:26.977
[ Music stops ]

09:27.001 --> 09:28.042
Whatever.

09:30.333 --> 09:31.875
[ Police radio chatter ]

09:31.958 --> 09:33.458
Aw, nuts!

09:33.542 --> 09:34.748
Wow! These are great.

09:34.772 --> 09:36.000
Do you have an agent?

09:36.083 --> 09:37.102
Believe me,

09:37.126 --> 09:38.167
I've been looking.

09:38.250 --> 09:40.060
- I know someone - who's really good.

09:40.167 --> 09:41.852
- Here. - Take some head shots.

09:41.958 --> 09:44.500
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

09:49.042 --> 09:51.125
Oh!

09:51.708 --> 09:52.998
Do you think they have

09:53.022 --> 09:54.333
a drama club in prison?

09:57.250 --> 09:58.250
[ Beeps ]

09:58.333 --> 09:59.415
I've learned

09:59.439 --> 10:00.542
a valuable lesson today.

10:00.625 --> 10:01.769
I'm never letting my ego

10:01.793 --> 10:02.958
get in my way again.

10:03.042 --> 10:04.269
The fact is,

10:04.293 --> 10:05.542
today I kicked bug butt

10:05.625 --> 10:07.917
and saved everybody's 401(k)s,

10:08.000 --> 10:09.477
but I couldn't have done it

10:09.501 --> 10:11.000
without... Gwen?

10:11.083 --> 10:12.144
Max:

10:12.168 --> 10:13.250
What's my motivation again?

10:13.333 --> 10:14.792
You want to make dinner.

10:14.875 --> 10:16.123
Hey, you missed my big scene,

10:16.147 --> 10:17.417
my great dialogue.

10:17.500 --> 10:18.667
You missed all...

10:18.750 --> 10:20.394
- Yeah, I don't want - to direct a comedy

10:20.500 --> 10:21.977
- Or an action movie - anymore.

10:22.083 --> 10:23.125
What?!

10:23.208 --> 10:24.560
- I'm making - a cooking show now.

10:24.667 --> 10:26.185
- Ee-yoink! - What?!

10:26.292 --> 10:27.519
Oh, there's no space left.

10:27.543 --> 10:28.792
I'll just delete the old movie.

10:28.875 --> 10:30.185
- [ Beeps ] - There we go.

10:30.292 --> 10:32.500
Aw, what?!

10:32.583 --> 10:33.833
Okay, Grandpa.

10:33.917 --> 10:35.394
- [ Beeps ] - And... action!

10:35.500 --> 10:36.958
Uhh, hi.

10:37.042 --> 10:39.540
I'm Grandpa Max, and this is

10:39.564 --> 10:42.083
"Cooking with MAXimum Flavor."

10:42.167 --> 10:43.519
Now, uh, you're going to grab

10:43.543 --> 10:44.917
your goat's beard,

10:45.000 --> 10:46.206
and, of course,

